The paper discusses a combination of Dynamic Adaptive Streaming over HTTP (DASH) and peer-to-peer (P2P) paradigm for video streaming. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new rate control strategy implemented at the peer site, which could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper investigates the system behavior in the critical condition of a flash crowd, which could be related to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
